US spot LPG activity quiet amid industry events . U . S . spot liquefied petroleum gas prices were steady in very quiet trade on Monday due to several industry seminars and outings , players said . There were at least three golf tournaments and seminars on Monday for the LPG market and few players were in their offices . In the U . S . Gulf Coast , Mont Belvieu , Texas , spot propane was talked steady at 33 . 75 / 34 . 00 cents a gallon . Conway , Kansas , was too thin to peg . Meanwhile , an explosion at Shell Oil Co ' s chemical plant in Houston had little impact on the market . The blast occurred on Sunday in the olefin unit where ethylene and propylene are produced . - - Laney Salisbury , New York Energy Desk + 1 212 859 1631 
